1. MULLED WINE Serves 6Ingredients:1 bottle of dry red wine1 cinnamon stick1 star anise2 cloves2 orange, thinly sliced60ml (4tbsp) sugarMethod:1) Pour the wine into a pan and add the spices and orange slices. Over low heat, add the sugar and stir to dissolve. Cook for 20 minutes.2) Ladle into heatproof glasses, with a slice of orange in each, and serve warm. 2. SPICY FISH STIR-FRY Serves 4Ingredients:15ml (1 tbsp) oil1 onion, finely chopped2 cloves garlic, crushed2cm piece of fresh ginger, peeled and grated1 star anise1 red chilli, seeded and chopped400g hake fillets, partially defrosted and cut into blocks200g spinach, chopped (or 250g pak choi, chopped)45ml (3 tbsp) oyster sauce45ml (3 tbsp) waterMethod:1) Preheat a wok and add the oil. Stir-fry the onion, garlic, ginger, star anise and chilli for 1-2 minutes.2) Add the hake fillets and stir-fry till the fish is almost cooked.3) Add the spinach or pak choi, oyster sauce and water. Stir-fry for another couple of minutes. 3. COCONUT PUFFS IN SPICY SYRUP Makes 12-14Ingredients:120g (1 cup) flour70g ( cup) self-raising flourA pinch of ground cinnamonA pinch ground cardamom60ml (4 tbsp) desiccated coconut1 x 400g can coconut milk15ml (1 tbsp) hot waterSyrup:125ml ( cup) water200g (1 cup) caster sugar1 clove1 star anise1 cinnamon stick3 exotic ways to cook with pomegranatesMethod:1) To make the batter for the coconut puffs, sift together the flour, self-raising flour, cinnamon and cardamom. Stir in the desiccated coconut and whisk in the coconut milk and the hot water, adding a little more water if the mixture is too thick.2) For the syrup, combine the water, caster sugar and spices in a pan. Stir over a low heat until the sugar has dissolved and boil for 3-5 minutes.3) Preheat oil for deep-frying and drop spoonfuls of coconut batter into the hot oil. Cook until golden brown on both sides.4) Stir the puffs in the syrup, remove and serve.